  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed extensions, by reason of their bulk, scale, massing, and position alongside the detailed design would result in an obtrusive and incompatible form of development that would fail to respect the character and appearance of the subject property and Graham Road and Mapledown Conservation Area. As such, the proposed development is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) and D4 (Delivering good design) of the London Plan 2021, LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020), and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD 2009.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14.666667px; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The proposed roof terrace, by reason of its size, elevation and location, would result in a loss of privacy and adverse noise and disturbance impacts to neighbouring occupiers, contrary to Policy D14 of the London Plan, Policies LP2 and LP58 of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 and the Council’s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
